HEADWORD: Ryot
<hw>Ry"ot</hw> <pr>(r⟦imac⟧"⟦ocr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar. &
Hind. <ets>ra'iyat</ets>, the same word as <ets>ra'iyah</ets>, a
subject, tenant, peasant. See <er>Rayah</er>.]</ety> <def>A peasant or
cultivator of the soil.</def> <mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Indian <qex>ryot</qex> and the Egyptian fellah work for less
pay than any other laborers in the world.</q> <rj><qau>The
Nation.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rypophagous</ent>⟦br⟧
